{"timestamp": "2025-12-04 09:28:16.980784", "event": "llm_start", "messages": "content='Based on the diagnosis report: Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\\n\\nScope and objective\\n- Topology: 2-tier Clos pod (2 spines) plus a super-spine, all EBGP (FRR). Each leaf connects to one host via 10.<pod>.<leaf>.0/24.\\n- Hosts: pc_0_0 (at leaf_router_0_0), pc_0_1 (at leaf_router_0_1).\\n- Goal: Detect anomalies, localize faulty devices, identify root cause.\\n\\nSummary of findings\\n- The fabric control plane (BGP) and inter-leaf routing are healthy.\\n- The access segment to pc_0_1 is abnormal: the host NIC is not configured/up; L2/L3 to 10.0.1.2 is unreachable.\\n- End-to-end: pc_0_0 can reach both leaf SVIs (10.0.0.1 and 10.0.1.1) across the fabric, but cannot reach 10.0.1.2 because the endpoint is down.\\n\\nEvidence and details\\n\\nHost interfaces and IP config\\n- pc_0_0\\n  - IP/route: 10.0.0.2/24, default via 10.0.0.1. Interface up (eth0).\\n  - Ping tests:\\n    - pc_0_0 -> 10.0.0.1: OK (low RTT).\\n    - pc_0_0 -> 10.0.1.1: OK (low RTT).\\n    - pc_0_0 -> 10.0.1.2: Fails with “Destination Host Unreachable” from 172.16.0.7 (leaf_router_0_1).\\n- pc_0_1\\n  - No L3 config present; only loopback exists. No eth0 shown; no IP, no routes.\\n  - Indicates host NIC down/unconfigured or disconnected.\\n\\nLeaf access interfaces and ARP\\n- leaf_router_0_1 (host-facing 10.0.1.1/24 on eth2)\\n  - ifconfig counters: RX/TX on eth2 are 0, consistent with no host traffic.\\n  - ARP/neighbor table: 10.0.1.2 FAILED (cannot resolve host MAC).\\n  - Local ping to 10.0.1.2 returns “Destination Host Unreachable.”\\n- leaf_router_0_0 (host-facing 10.0.0.1/24 on eth2)\\n  - ARP shows 10.0.0.2 lladdr 9e:e7:8e:0e:bb:93 STALE (host reachable at L2/L3 from this leaf).\\n\\nFabric control plane (BGP) and routing\\n- All EBGP sessions are established:\\n  - Leaves:\\n    - leaf_router_0_0 (AS 65200) peers with spines 172.16.0.4 (AS 65100) and 172.16.0.8 (AS 65101); receives 1 prefix; advertises 10.0.0.0/24.\\n    - leaf_router_0_1 (AS 65201) peers with spines 172.16.0.6 (AS 65100) and 172.16.0.10 (AS 65101); receives 1 prefix; advertises 10.0.1.0/24.\\n  - Spines:\\n    - spine_router_0_0 (AS 65100) peers with super-spine 172.16.0.0, leaves 172.16.0.5 and 172.16.0.7; installs both 10.0.0.0/24 and 10.0.1.0/24 learned from leaves.\\n    - spine_router_0_1 (AS 65101) peers with super-spine 172.16.0.2, leaves 172.16.0.9 and 172.16.0.11; installs both /24s learned from leaves.\\n  - Super-spine (AS 65000) peers with both spines and has both 10.0.0.0/24 and 10.0.1.0/24 in RIB.\\n- Note on BGP summary asymmetry:\\n  - spine_router_0_0 shows 0 PfxRcd from the super-spine; spine_router_0_1 shows 2 PfxRcd. This is consistent with EBGP best-path selection and standard behavior: the super-spine selects a best path (from one spine) and advertises to the other spine; it does not advertise a route back to the neighbor it learned it from. This is expected and not a fault.\\n\\nData-plane reachability across fabric\\n- spine_router_0_0 -> 10.0.1.1: OK.\\n- spine_router_0_1 -> 10.0.0.1: OK.\\n- pc_0_0 -> 10.0.1.1: OK.\\n- Failures are isolated to reaching 10.0.1.2 (the endpoint on leaf_router_0_1’s access network).\\n\\nDetected anomalies\\n- pc_0_1 host NIC/interface missing or down; no IP assigned; no routing; no ARP replies.\\n- leaf_router_0_1 reports ARP failure to 10.0.1.2 and zero traffic counters on host-facing interface.\\n\\nFault localization\\n- Faulty segment: Access link on pod 0, leaf_router_0_1 eth2 -> pc_0_1.\\n- Affected device: pc_0_1 (host endpoint).\\n- Fabric devices (leaves, spines, super-spine) appear operational with correct EBGP adjacencies and routing.\\n\\nRoot cause\\n- Endpoint misconfiguration or link down on pc_0_1. The host NIC is not up/configured (no eth0 present, no IP), causing ARP resolution failures on leaf_router_0_1 and making 10.0.1.2 unreachable. The Clos fabric itself is healthy., please provide the submission. Do not submit if no report available.' additional_kwargs={} response_metadata={} id='3023583d-0780-43e4-b10d-219f4ac68901'", "model": {"lc": 1, "type": "constructor", "id": ["langchain", "chat_models", "openai", "ChatOpenAI"], "kwargs": {"model_name": "gpt-5", "openai_api_key": {"lc": 1, "type": "secret", "id": ["OPENAI_API_KEY"]}, "stream_usage": true}, "name": "ChatOpenAI"}}
